"indicator, especially on the cooperation arrangements, transboundary waters "
"covered by them as well as operationality. The Convention&#x2019;s regular "
"reporting on transboundary water cooperation, involving both Parties and non-"
"Parties to the Convention, will collect this information every 3 years as of "
"2017. The reporting covers transboundary rivers, lakes and groundwaters. "
"UNESCO IHP will contribute to the reporting on transboundary aquifers. More "
"than 100 countries participate in the Water Convention&#x2019;s activities. "
"The United Nations Economic Commission for Europe acts as Secretariat for "
"the Water Convention. Some countries already report to regional "
"organizations (e.g. the European Union or the Southern African Development "
